sources.data_found: Computer science program offers programming, analysis, design, security courses. Faculty continually evaluate and update course offerings.

Total enrollment 3,674 students (2,590 undergraduate, 1,084 graduate). Most popular majors: Registered Nursing (205 degrees), General Biological Sciences (51 degrees), General Psychology (49 degrees).
Fisher has five schools. School of Arts and Sciences is the largest school offering degrees in over 20 undergraduate academic disciplines.
Campus community home to over 2,600 full-time undergraduates, nearly 200 part-time undergraduates, and over 1,000 graduate students.
